==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thule
<hw>Thu"le</hw> <pr>(th⟦umac⟧"l⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Thule</ets>, <ets>Thyle</ets>, Gr. <grk>Qoy`lh</grk>,
<grk>Qy`lh</grk>.]</ety> <def>The name given by ancient geographers to
the northernmost part of the habitable world. According to some, this
land was Norway, according to others, Iceland, or more probably
Mainland, the largest of the Shetland islands; hence, the Latin phrase
<xex>ultima Thule</xex>, farthest Thule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thulia</ent>⟦br⟧
